<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb937c5c8-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s13126"><num value="13126">§ 13126.</num><heading> Reports to Congress</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Director shall, no later than April 30 of each year in which the second session of a Congress begins, submit to the Congress a report containing—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb937c5c9-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s13126/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> a summary of the actions taken by the Director during a 2-year period ending on December 31 of the preceding year in order to carry out the Director’s functions and responsibilities under this subchapter; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb937c5ca-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s13126/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> such other information as the Director may consider appropriate.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idb937c5cb-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea">(<ref href="/us/pl/117/286/s3/c">Pub. L. 117–286, § 3(c)</ref>, <date date="2022-12-27">Dec. 27, 2022</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/136/4302">136 Stat. 4302</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
